DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGgraphmacros.pl",
  "freemanMacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);


TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
$a=random(5,7,1);
$b=random(3,4,1);
$c=$a-1;
$d=$b-1;
$s="-1/(2*(x**$a+x**$b)^2) ";

BEGIN_TEXT
\{ textbook_ref_exact("Rogawski ET 2e", "5.6","36") \}$BR

Evaluate the indefinite integral:
$PAR

\(\int \frac {$a x^{$c} + $b x^{$d} } {(x^{$a} + x^{$b})^3} \,dx =\)   \{ans_rule()\}  \(+ C\)

END_TEXT
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR$BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD $PAR
Let \(u=x^{$a} + x^{$b}\), then \( du= ($a x^{$c} + $b x^{$d}) \,dx\). Hence $BR
\( \int \frac {$a x^{$c} + $b x^{$d} } {(x^{$a} + x^{$b})^3} \,dx = \int \frac {du}{u^3} = - \frac {1}{2} u^{-2}+C = \frac {-1}{2 (x^{$a} + x^{$b})^2}+C \)

END_SOLUTION

ANS(fun_cmp($s));

ENDDOCUMENT();

